HAND, FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - THAILAND
************************************************************
Date: Fri 23 Nov 2007
Soutve: China View, Xinhua News Agency [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2007-11/23/content_7134919.htm>


Schools closed after hand, foot & mouth disease outbreak in Thailand
------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------
Several schools in central and northern Thailand have been ordered to
close after the outbreak of hand, foot & mouth disease (HFMD), local
media reported on Friday [23 Nov 2007]. The Public Health Office in
northern Lampang Province Friday [23 Nov 2007] ordered the Prachawit
School to close its kindergarten classes after about 10 kids were
found to have contracted the disease, local news network "The Nation" reported.

On Thursday [22 Nov 2007], the office ordered Assumption School in
Lampang to close its kindergarten classes following the outbreak of
the disease. Also in Lambang, local authorities on Friday [23 Nov
2007] ordered a nursery to close after 16 children there contracted HFMD.

Meanwhile, in central Chon Buri Province, several schools in Sattahib
district were ordered to be on alert following an outbreak of HFMD at
a school. About 10 students of Ban Sattahib School got the disease
and received treatment at 2 hospitals in the district, prompting the
district health office to inform other schools to be on alert.

